The White House Press Secretary released a statement regarding the U.S. Court of Appeals for the District of Columbia's decision on U.S. Telecom Association v. FCC. The statement highlights that the ruling is a victory for an open and fair Internet, allowing for innovation and economic growth without service providers acting as paid gatekeepers. It acknowledges the millions of Americans who voiced their support for a free and fair Internet. The statement also mentions that companies that connect people to the Internet have obligations not to exploit their monopoly over access. It emphasizes that net neutrality has been the norm for most of the Internet's existence and that an Open Internet is crucial for encouraging new investment, online services, and content. The President has strongly supported net neutrality and continues to work towards protecting the Internet ecosystem as it is seen as one of the greatest gifts to the economy and society.